\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {6}{\ignorespaces Qualitative reconstruction across all eight PPT configurations. Each row shows a held-out chest X-ray (left column) and the decoder's pixel-wise reconstruction under each configuration (each defense evaluated under its own threat model; SMPC columns show the single-corrupted-server view). Configurations without DP or SMPC (\texttt  {baseline}, \texttt  {bie-only}) reproduce coarse anatomical structure visibly; DP-only and dp+bie produce blurred but partially recognizable silhouettes; every SMPC-enabled column collapses to a featureless mean-image, consistent with the information-theoretic independence of the single-server share from $E(x)$.}}{7}{}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{fig:recon_grid}{{6}{7}{}{figure.6}{}}
